## Post-cp1 fix — PUPPETEER_SKIP_DOWNLOAD env var name

`PUPPETEER_SKIP_CHROMIUM_DOWNLOAD` is the puppeteer v24 name. puppeteer v25 renamed
it to `PUPPETEER_SKIP_DOWNLOAD`. The postinstall script in v25 ignores the old name,
so the API builder attempted Chrome download despite the env var being set, then
failed because Linux lacks the Windows extraction binaries (`powershell.exe`,
`pwsh.exe`).

The old Dockerfile (slice 1a, before cp1 restructure) was unaffected: that file
used `PUPPETEER_SKIP_CHROMIUM_DOWNLOAD=true` only in the runtime stage, where
`pnpm install` never runs — Chrome was already present from the builder copy.
The bug only surfaces in the new API Dockerfile where the skip var is relied upon
in the builder stage to prevent the download.

Fix applied (same session, post-cp1 commit):
- `apps/api/Dockerfile`: `PUPPETEER_SKIP_CHROMIUM_DOWNLOAD` → `PUPPETEER_SKIP_DOWNLOAD`
  (ENV declaration + comment)
- `apps/api/Dockerfile.render`: same rename in the runtime stage ENV and comment.
  Builder stage of Dockerfile.render intentionally has no SKIP var (Chrome must
  download there).

